*** Bug 92753 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
I'm not sure what you meant by step 2.
2.import TestData/CA

However, when I create these two files, I am getting the completion list. This
is with whatever we have in the HEAD.
I found the problem at last. The "ALT + /" was already being used for "Hippie 
Completion", therefore resulting in a conflict. I changed the Hot Key from "ALT 
+ /" to "Ctrl + ALT + Y" and then it worked. Thanks for your help.



In Chinese OS, the IME has a shortcut of Ctl+Space to switch between English and
Chinese input, so the translation of our Content Assist shortcut is "Alt+/".
This "Hippie Completion" menu item should change its shortcut to avoid conflict.
Tanya, would you let me know which file is involved here. We are running TVT 
now and can fix translation.

