source_code.code:
class B: private A {
   public : 
      A::z;   //adjust access
}

Bug.WithStack:
spec 11.3.
class A {
   public : int z;
};
class B: private A {
   public : 
      A::z;   //adjust access
}

Note that (11.3-1) an access declaration is equivalent to a using declaration. 
Perhaps we should parse it as one, the semantics would come for free then. 
(Access declarations are deprecated in favour of using declarations)
Future means you commit to fix it in the Future. Inboxes can't make committments. Moving to '--'.
Fixed in 5.0.1 > 20080710

